{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Thu Sep 26 13:01:54 +0000 2019", "created_at_iso": "2019-09-26T13:01:54Z", "created_at_ts": 1569502914, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1177206661603348480", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 5195, \"reply_count\": 636, \"like_count\": 8608, \"quote_count\": 1615, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "1/ As a former CIA analyst and former NSC official who edited transcripts of POTUS phone calls with foreign leaders, here are my thoughts on the whistleblower complaint which was just released. . . https://t.co/MdMdanGME4", "tweet_type": "tweet", "urls_json": "[{\"url\": \"https://t.co/MdMdanGME4\", \"expanded_url\": \"https://intelligence.house.gov/uploadedfiles/20190812_-_whistleblower_complaint_unclass.pdf\", \"display_url\": \"intelligence.house.gov/uploadedfiles/…\"}]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Thu Sep 26 13:03:57 +0000 2019", "created_at_iso": "2019-09-26T13:03:57Z", "created_at_ts": 1569503037, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1177207176873553920", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 1425, \"reply_count\": 79, \"like_count\": 4112, \"quote_count\": 53, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "2/ This is not an intelligence matter.  It is a policy matter and a complaint about differences over policy.  Presidential phone calls are not an intelligence concern.  The fact that IC officers transcribe these calls does not give the IC IG jusrisdiction over these calls.", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Thu Sep 26 13:05:22 +0000 2019", "created_at_iso": "2019-09-26T13:05:22Z", "created_at_ts": 1569503122, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1177207537193639936", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 1251, \"reply_count\": 33, \"like_count\": 3907, \"quote_count\": 41, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "3/ It appears that rules restricting access and knowledge of these sensitive calls was breached.  This official was not on this call, not on the approved dissem list and should not have been briefed on the call.", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Thu Sep 26 13:08:03 +0000 2019", "created_at_iso": "2019-09-26T13:08:03Z", "created_at_ts": 1569503283, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1177208211524505600", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 1553, \"reply_count\": 130, \"like_count\": 4384, \"quote_count\": 118, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": ".3/ The way this complaint was written suggested the author had a lot of help.  I know from my work on the House Intel Commitee staff that many whistleblowers go directly to the intel oversight committees.  Did this whistleblower first meet with House Intel committee members?", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Thu Sep 26 13:09:54 +0000 2019", "created_at_iso": "2019-09-26T13:09:54Z", "created_at_ts": 1569503394, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1177208676643409921", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 1277, \"reply_count\": 88, \"like_count\": 3961, \"quote_count\": 54, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": ".4/ It is therefore important that Congress find out where this complaint came from.  What did House and Senate intel committee dem members and staff know about it and when?  Did they help orchestrate this complaint?", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Thu Sep 26 13:12:23 +0000 2019", "created_at_iso": "2019-09-26T13:12:23Z", "created_at_ts": 1569503543, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1177209302630768640", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 1332, \"reply_count\": 70, \"like_count\": 4044, \"quote_count\": 69, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "5/ My view is that this whistleblower complaint is too convenient and too perfect to come from a typical whistleblower.  Were other IC officers involved?  Where outside groups opposed to the president involved?", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Thu Sep 26 13:14:37 +0000 2019", "created_at_iso": "2019-09-26T13:14:37Z", "created_at_ts": 1569503677, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1177209864176766977", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 1251, \"reply_count\": 33, \"like_count\": 3840, \"quote_count\": 37, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "6/ This complaint will further damage IC relations with the White House for many years to come because IC officers appear to be politicizing presidential phone calls with foreign officials and their access to the president and his activities in the White House.", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Thu Sep 26 13:16:59 +0000 2019", "created_at_iso": "2019-09-26T13:16:59Z", "created_at_ts": 1569503819, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1177210456571858944", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 1258, \"reply_count\": 40, \"like_count\": 4039, \"quote_count\": 35, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "7/ Worst of all, this IC officer -- and probably others --  have blatantly crossed the line into policy.  This violates a core  responsibility of IC officers is to inform, but not make policy.", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Thu Sep 26 13:19:03 +0000 2019", "created_at_iso": "2019-09-26T13:19:03Z", "created_at_ts": 1569503943, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1177210980738240513", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 1796, \"reply_count\": 291, \"like_count\": 5691, \"quote_count\": 155, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "8/ This is such a grevious violation of trust between the IC and  the White House that it would not surprise me if IC officers are barred from all access to POTUS phone calls with foreign officials.", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
